[Civ. No. 2999. First Appellate District, Division One. September 2, 1919.] ROGERS BROTHERS COMPANY et al., Respondents, v. JOHN H. BECK, et al., Appellants. [1] Street Law—Action to Foreclose Lien—Pleading—Evidence. Judgment affirmed on the authority of Sogers Brothers Co. et at. v. Beck et al., ante, p. 110. APPEAL from a judgment of the Superior Court of Imperial County. W. H. Thomas, Judge Presiding. Affirmed. *800The facts are the same as those stated in Rogers Brothers Co. et al, v. Beck et al., ante, p. 110, [184 Pac. 515].

James E. O’Keefe and C. H. Van Winkle for Appellants.

Crouch & Crouch for Respondents.

THE COURT.

[1] On the authority of Rogers Brothers Co. et al. v. Beck et al., ante, p. 110, [184 Pac. 515], the judgment is affirmed.
